{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17586117","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17586117"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T08:25:58+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T08:25:58+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15060"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15060","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15060"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.33,0.25,0.21,0.08,0.13]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7748"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67751"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7748","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7748"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15060"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53216"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4933"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8115"},{"type":"tags","id":"8126"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"18916"},{"type":"contributions","id":"18918"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67751","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/67751"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EChronic hyperglycaemia causes thickening of the glomerular basement membrane, which initiates a series of pathological changes in the kidney.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the correct sequence of pathological changes in diabetic nephropathy?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Glomerular hypertrophy \u2192 endothelial injury \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production","Endothelial injury \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production \u2192 hypertrophy","Glomerular hypertrophy \u2192 endothelial injury \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 matrix production","Glomerular hypertrophy \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 endothelial injury \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production","Glomerular hypertrophy \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production \u2192 endothelial injury"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct pathological sequence in diabetic nephropathy is \u003Cstrong\u003Eglomerular hypertrophy \u2192 endothelial injury \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production\u003C/strong\u003E. This sequence reflects the progressive nature of diabetic kidney disease.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect sequences can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEndothelial injury \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production \u2192 hypertrophy\u003C/strong\u003E - Glomerular hypertrophy occurs early as an adaptive response\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGlomerular hypertrophy \u2192 endothelial injury \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 matrix production\u003C/strong\u003E - Protein accumulation must precede mesangial proliferation\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGlomerular hypertrophy \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 endothelial injury \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production\u003C/strong\u003E - Endothelial injury causes protein accumulation, not vice versa\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGlomerular hypertrophy \u2192 protein accumulation \u2192 mesangial proliferation \u2192 matrix production \u2192 endothelial injury\u003C/strong\u003E - Endothelial injury is an early event that triggers protein accumulation\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EUnderstanding this sequence helps explain how chronic hyperglycaemia leads to progressive kidney damage and eventual glomerulosclerosis.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["Diabetic nephropathy progresses through distinct stages starting with glomerular basement membrane thickening.","The sequence of glomerular hypertrophy, endothelial injury, protein accumulation, mesangial proliferation, and extracellular matrix production leads to glomerulosclerosis.","Understanding the sequence of pathological changes helps explain the progressive nature of diabetic kidney disease."],"references":["Pourghasem M, Shafi H, Babazadeh Z. Histological changes of kidney in diabetic nephropathy. Caspian J Intern Med. 2015 Summer;6(3):120-7. PMID: 26644877; PMCID: PMC4650785.","Jennette, J. C., \u0026 D\u0027Agati, V. D. (2023). Heptinstall\u0027s Pathology of the Kidney. Lippincott Williams \u0026 Wilkins","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science","Koeppen, B. M., \u0026 Stanton, B. A. (2018). Renal Physiology E-Book: Renal Physiology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53216"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15060"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"53216","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/53216"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-06T22:13:05+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-06T22:14:48+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7748"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"67751"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"descript